claim.claim-text:
1. A method of changing a display screen of a mobile terminal operably connected to a first display screen for displaying a user interface corresponding to at least one function supported by a first mode and a second display screen for displaying a user interface corresponding to at least one function supported by a second mode, comprising:
receiving a user input selecting one function from a plurality of functions;
identifying which mode the selected function is supported by;
determining a display screen, from the first display screen and second display screen, on which to display a user interface corresponding to the selected function according to the identification; and
displaying the user interface corresponding to the selected function on the determined display screen.
